---
// Founding section index — The Eighth Anchor Institute founding proposal.
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Founding Proposal — The Eighth Anchor Institute"
  description="The founding proposal for The Eighth Anchor Institute: an AI-staffed institution carrying the two-century empirical record of America's school trust lands into the design of the AI-era's forever-trusts."
  path="/founding/"
  ogTitle="Founding Proposal — The Eighth Anchor Institute"
  ogDescription="A founding proposal prepared for Tonia Day, CEO of Advocates for School Trust Lands, by Dave Sullivan, Founding Chairman. May 28, 2026."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-eai-navy text-eai-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-20 md:py-24">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-4">
        Founding Proposal · May 28, 2026
      </p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-eai-bone leading-tight">
        The Eighth Anchor Institute
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif italic text-eai-parchment/85 text-xl mt-3">
        A founding proposal.
      </p>
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none mt-8 text-eai-parchment/90 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Prepared for <strong>Tonia Day</strong>, CEO, Advocates for School Trust Lands.<br />
          From <strong>Dave Sullivan</strong>, Founding Chairman.
        </p>
        <p class="italic text-eai-parchment/75">
          An AI-staffed institute that brings the empirical record of America's school
          trust lands into the design of the AI-era's forever-trusts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About this document -->
  <section class="bg-eai-bone border-b border-eai-blueprint/20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-10">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-3">
        About this document
      </p>
      <p class="text-eai-navy/85 leading-relaxed">
        This is the founding proposal for The Eighth Anchor Institute, drafted by
        AI staff under the coordination of an AI chief executive called Cowork,
        with the chairman in the editor's chair. It is presented here for
        chairman and founding-board review. Mark it up freely.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Executive Summary -->
  <section class="bg-eai-bone">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-3">
        Executive Summary
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-eai-navy mb-8">The proposition</h2>
      <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-eai-navy/90 leading-relaxed font-serif">
        <p>
          The Eighth Anchor Institute is a proposed 501(c)(3) operating institution
          with a single job: carry the two-century empirical record of America's
          school trust lands into the design of the forever-trusts now being
          chartered for the AI era. The institute is staffed primarily by
          best-of-breed AI agents working under a human chairman, with humans
          recruited into specific advisory roles and fellowships. It is built to
          read more, write more, and remember more than any traditional research
          shop of its size — and to do so at a tempo that matches the speed at
          which the AI-era institutions are being designed.
        </p>
        <p>
          The architects of the AI-era's long-running fiduciary institutions are
          working now. Sovereign AI funds. Perpetual climate trusts. Longevity
          escrows. Compute reserves. These are being chartered in 2026, not 2040.
          The architects are smart people, and they are flying blind. There is no
          body of empirical data on how multi-generational trusts actually fail —
          except one. America's school trust lands are the only fiduciary
          experiment that has run long enough to produce the failure-mode record.
          Two centuries of data on gradual drift — rotted purpose, redefined
          beneficiary, modernized mandate — and on sudden directed seizure. If
          that record does not reach the architects inside the next eighteen
          months, the institutions they are chartering today will repeat the
          exact failures the school trust lands have already documented. The
          window is narrow and it is closing.
        </p>
        <p>
          ASTL's mission and the institute's mission compose cleanly. ASTL is the
          contemporary national coalition — the working membership, the
          state-by-state organizing, the advocacy presence. The institute is the
          research-and-recruitment vehicle that takes the field's empirical work
          and lands it inside the AI-era trust-design conversation. The two
          organizations are complementary, not competing, and the seams between
          them are visible from the outset. Your specific contribution, Tonia:
          institutional advancement, donor cultivation, and the board-level
          relationships you already hold in fiduciary-law and philanthropy
          circles. That is the half of this work no AI staff can do.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>What we are asking.</strong> A 30-day pilot of the operating
          model, followed by a clean incorporation decision at the end of it. The
          booklet you are reading is itself part of the pilot — it was drafted by
          AI staff under the coordination of an AI chief executive called Cowork,
          with the chairman in the editor's chair. If the operating model produces
          work of this caliber in 30 days, the case for incorporation makes
          itself. We want you on the founding board, in whatever form fits you
          best — advisor, co-founder, board chair pro tem, or something we have
          not named yet. The chairman wants your honest read on this booklet by
          the end of next week. Hedged feedback is not useful here. Direct is.
        </p>
        <p class="text-eai-blueprint italic">
          The summary above states the proposition. The four sections that follow
          give you the evidence to evaluate it: the thesis underneath the work,
          the programs that carry it out, the operating model that makes it
          possible at this scale, and the honest list of what could go wrong.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section nav cards -->
  <section class="bg-eai-parchment border-t border-eai-blueprint/20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-3">
        The four sections
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-eai-navy mb-8">Read in order</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <a href="/founding/vision/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 1</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Vision</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            The thesis: why the school-trust-lands record is the only empirical floor
            for AI-era trust design, why this institution does not yet exist, and
            why the clock is running.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/founding/programs/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 2</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Programs and First Year</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            Five programs — Library, Briefings, Fellowship, Convening, Recruitment —
            and the twelve-month calendar that proves the Institute can do what it
            says.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/founding/operations/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 3</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Operations</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            How the work actually gets made: a human chairman, an AI CEO called
            Cowork, six AI staff roles, public disclosure of the operating form,
            and a small honest budget.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/founding/risks-and-asks/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 4</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Risks and Asks</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            Five honest risks. Three specific asks of Tonia. A short, concrete
            sequence of next steps for the next sixty days.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 flex justify-end">
        <a href="/founding/vision/" class="font-serif text-eai-navy hover:text-eai-gold">
          Start with Section 1: Vision &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
